So I'm assuming you have paused it,

00:00:45.047 --> 00:00:46.181
and had a go at it.

00:00:46.604 --> 00:00:47.640
So let's think this through together.

00:00:48.233 --> 00:00:50.247
If we know that this kind of a solution

00:00:50.373 --> 00:00:51.526
can be described in this way,

00:00:51.526 --> 00:00:52.597
we need to figure out
some m's and b's here.

00:00:53.236 --> 00:00:54.792
This is telling us that if we were to take

00:00:54.792 --> 00:00:56.986
the derivative of this with respect to x,

00:00:56.986 --> 00:00:59.048
if we take the derivative of
mx plus b with respect to x,

00:00:59.606 --> 00:01:01.639
that that should be equal
to negative 2 times x

00:01:01.936 --> 00:01:03.367
plus 3 times y.

00:01:03.367 --> 00:01:06.614
well, we know y is this thing, minus 5.

00:01:06.614 --> 00:01:08.846
And that should be true for all x's,

00:01:08.846 --> 00:01:10.843
in order for this to be a solution

00:01:10.843 --> 00:01:12.230
to this differential equation.

00:01:12.023 --> 00:01:13.318
Remember, the solution to
a differential equation

00:01:13.525 --> 00:01:15.359
is not a value or a set of values.

00:01:15.359 --> 00:01:19.202
It is a function or a set of functions.

00:01:19.202 --> 00:01:22.747
So in order for this to satisfy
this differential equation,

00:01:22.747 --> 00:01:25.463
it needs to be true for
all of these x's here.

00:01:25.463 --> 00:01:26.679
So let's work through it.

00:01:26.679 --> 00:01:30.126
Let's figure out first what our dy dx is.

00:01:30.126 --> 00:01:31.839
So dy dx.

00:01:32.247 --> 00:01:34.533
We'll just take the derivative
here with respect to x

00:01:34.533 --> 00:01:37.676
dy dx is derivative of
mx with respect to x,

00:01:37.676 --> 00:01:39.448
is just going to be m.

00:01:39.448 --> 00:01:41.561
And of course derivative
of b with respect to x,

00:01:41.561 --> 00:01:42.694
just a constant,

00:01:42.694 --> 00:01:43.757
so it's just going to be zero.

00:01:44.324 --> 00:01:46.951
So dy dx is m.

00:01:46.951 --> 00:01:51.243
So we could write m is
equal to negative 2x,

00:01:51.243 --> 00:01:54.339
is equal to negative 2x,

00:01:54.339 --> 00:01:57.378
plus 3 times, and instead
of putting y there

00:01:57.729 --> 00:01:58.798
I could write mx plus b.

00:01:59.419 --> 00:02:02.112
Remember y is equal to mx plus b.

00:02:02.112 --> 00:02:03.723
And just as a repeated reminder,

00:02:03.723 --> 00:02:05.735
this has to be true for all x's.

00:02:05.843 --> 00:02:10.842
mx plus b, and then of
course we have the minus 5.

00:02:11.973 --> 00:02:14.546
So if you weren't able to
