00:03:02.456 --> 00:03:05.955
that's going to be
negative 2 plus 3m times x,

00:03:05.955 --> 00:03:10.955
or we could write this
as 3m minus 2 times x,

00:03:11.319 --> 00:03:13.675
and then you have your constant terms,

00:03:13.675 --> 00:03:15.161
so you have these terms right over here,

00:03:15.161 --> 00:03:18.733
so plus 3b minus 5,

00:03:18.733 --> 00:03:20.985
and of course that's all
going to be equal to m.

00:03:20.985 --> 00:03:23.709
That's going to be equal to m.

00:03:23.709 --> 00:03:25.716
Now remember, this needs to be true,

00:03:25.716 --> 00:03:29.258
this needs to be true for all x's.

00:03:29.945 --> 00:03:31.592
So notice, over here I have

00:03:31.592 --> 00:03:35.110
some coefficient times x
on the right-hand side.

00:03:35.011 --> 00:03:38.024
But on the left-hand side I have no x's.

00:03:38.123 --> 00:03:40.759
So somehow, this thing must disappear.

00:03:40.759 --> 00:03:43.982
This is a constant, so
it's completely reasonable.

00:03:43.982 --> 00:03:46.005
It's completely reasonable
that this constant

00:03:46.212 --> 00:03:48.695
could be equal to m.

00:03:48.695 --> 00:03:51.609
But the only way that I
get these x's to disappear

00:03:51.609 --> 00:03:54.005
so all I'm left with is an m,

00:03:54.005 --> 00:03:56.507
is if this thing is equal to zero.

00:03:56.621 --> 00:03:57.584
Let me say that again,

00:03:57.584 --> 00:03:59.213
